  "text": "Proof. Since the case µ 0 = 0 was proved in [CITATION_1] , we only need to show the case µ 0 ̸ = 0. Again as discussed previously, it suffices to prove the theorem only with s = 3. To this end, by the assumption µ 0H2 ≤ 0, we firstly want to show there exists some ξ(t) ∈ S for any fixed t ∈ [0, T ) with the maximum existence time T > 0 and ξ(0) = ξ 0 such that µ 0 u(t, ξ(t)) ≤ 0 for any fixed t ∈ [0, T ). If not, then µ 0 u(t, x) > 0 with any x ∈ S and some t ∈ [0, T ). Recall that",
